56,-0.028) M^(0.8(+1.1,-0.9)) 10^((3.8 +/- 1.2)F). Our results are\nconsistent with gravitational microlensing measurements of the planet\noccurrence rate; this study represents the first model-independent comparison\nwith microlensing observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Jul 2013 20:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Jan 2014 23:52:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-01-23"}
