s Dicke effect) and\nnegative $k$ zones. This particularly throws light on the nature of the\nend-state of collapse in accelerated expansion in Brans Dicke gravity. It is\nseen that for positive values of EoS parameter $k$, the collapse results in a\nblack hole, whereas for negative values of $k$, naked singularity is the only\noutcome. It is also to be noted that \"low $\\omega$\" leads to the possibility of\ngetting more naked singularities even for a non-accelerating universe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 23 Jul 2013 13:31:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 18 Aug 2014 13:14:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
